108 NTSTATUS
109 PspQueryWorkingSetWatch(
110  IN HANDLE ProcessHandle,
111  IN PROCESSINFOCLASS ProcessInformationClass,
112  OUT PVOID ProcessInformation,
113  IN ULONG ProcessInformationLength,
114  OUT PULONG ReturnLength OPTIONAL,
115  IN KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode
116  )
117 {
118  PPAGEFAULT_HISTORY WorkingSetCatcher;
119  ULONG SpaceNeeded;
120  PEPROCESS Process;
121  KIRQL OldIrql;
122  NTSTATUS st;
123 
124  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER (ProcessInformationClass);
125 
126  st = ObReferenceObjectByHandle (ProcessHandle,
127  PROCESS_QUERY_INFORMATION,
128  PsProcessType,
129  PreviousMode,
130  (PVOID *)&Process,
131  NULL);
132 
133  if (!NT_SUCCESS (st)) {
134  return st;
135  }
136 
137  WorkingSetCatcher = Process->WorkingSetWatch;
138  if (WorkingSetCatcher == NULL) {
139  ObDereferenceObject (Process);
140  return STATUS_UNSUCCESSFUL;
141  }
142 
143  MmLockPageableSectionByHandle (ExPageLockHandle);
144  ExAcquireSpinLock (&WorkingSetCatcher->SpinLock,&OldIrql);
145 
146  if (WorkingSetCatcher->CurrentIndex) {
147 
148  //
149  // Null Terminate the first empty entry in the buffer
150  //
151 
152  WorkingSetCatcher->WatchInfo[WorkingSetCatcher->CurrentIndex].FaultingPc = NULL;
153 
154  //Store a special Va value if the buffer was full and
155  //page faults could have been lost
156 
157  if (WorkingSetCatcher->CurrentIndex != WorkingSetCatcher->MaxIndex) {
158  WorkingSetCatcher->WatchInfo[WorkingSetCatcher->CurrentIndex].FaultingVa = NULL;
159  } else {
160  WorkingSetCatcher->WatchInfo[WorkingSetCatcher->CurrentIndex].FaultingVa = (PVOID) 1;
161  }
162 
163  SpaceNeeded = (WorkingSetCatcher->CurrentIndex+1) * sizeof(PROCESS_WS_WATCH_INFORMATION);
164  } else {
165  ExReleaseSpinLock (&WorkingSetCatcher->SpinLock, OldIrql);
166  MmUnlockPageableImageSection (ExPageLockHandle);
167  ObDereferenceObject (Process);
168  return STATUS_NO_MORE_ENTRIES;
169  }
170 
171  if (ProcessInformationLength < SpaceNeeded) {
172  ExReleaseSpinLock (&WorkingSetCatcher->SpinLock, OldIrql);
173  MmUnlockPageableImageSection (ExPageLockHandle);
174  ObDereferenceObject (Process);
175  return STATUS_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL;
176  }
177 
178  //
179  // Mark the Working Set buffer as full and then drop the lock
180  // and copy the bytes
181  //
182 
183  WorkingSetCatcher->CurrentIndex = MAX_WS_CATCH_INDEX;
184 
185  ExReleaseSpinLock (&WorkingSetCatcher->SpinLock,OldIrql);
186 
187  try {
188  RtlCopyMemory (ProcessInformation, &WorkingSetCatcher->WatchInfo[0], SpaceNeeded);
189  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT (ReturnLength) ) {
190  *ReturnLength = SpaceNeeded;
191  }
192  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
193  st = GetExceptionCode ();
194  }
195 
196  ExAcquireSpinLock (&WorkingSetCatcher->SpinLock, &OldIrql);
197  WorkingSetCatcher->CurrentIndex = 0;
198  ExReleaseSpinLock (&WorkingSetCatcher->SpinLock, OldIrql);
199 
200  MmUnlockPageableImageSection (ExPageLockHandle);
201  ObDereferenceObject (Process);
202 
203  return st;
204 }

206 NTSTATUS
207 PspQueryQuotaLimits(
208  IN HANDLE ProcessHandle,
209  IN PROCESSINFOCLASS ProcessInformationClass,
210  OUT PVOID ProcessInformation,
211  IN ULONG ProcessInformationLength,
212  OUT PULONG ReturnLength OPTIONAL,
213  IN KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode
214  )
215 {
216  QUOTA_LIMITS_EX QuotaLimits={0};
217  PEPROCESS Process;
218  NTSTATUS Status;
219  PEPROCESS_QUOTA_BLOCK QuotaBlock;
220  SIZE_T PeakWorkingSetSize;
221  SIZE_T WorkingSetSize;
222  ULONG HardEnforcement;
223  KAPC_STATE ApcState;
224 
225  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER (ProcessInformationClass);
226 
227  if (ProcessInformationLength != sizeof (QUOTA_LIMITS) &&
228  ProcessInformationLength != sizeof (QUOTA_LIMITS_EX)) {
229  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
230  }
231 
232  Status = ObReferenceObjectByHandle (ProcessHandle,
233  PROCESS_QUERY_INFORMATION,
234  PsProcessType,
235  PreviousMode,
236  &Process,
237  NULL);
238  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
239  return Status;
240  }
241 
242  QuotaBlock = Process->QuotaBlock;
243 
244  if (QuotaBlock != &PspDefaultQuotaBlock) {
245  QuotaLimits.PagedPoolLimit = QuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsPagedPool].Limit;
246  QuotaLimits.NonPagedPoolLimit = QuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsNonPagedPool].Limit;
247  QuotaLimits.PagefileLimit = QuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsPageFile].Limit;
248  } else {
249  QuotaLimits.PagedPoolLimit = (SIZE_T)-1;
250  QuotaLimits.NonPagedPoolLimit = (SIZE_T)-1;
251  QuotaLimits.PagefileLimit = (SIZE_T)-1;
252  }
253 
254  QuotaLimits.TimeLimit.LowPart = 0xffffffff;
255  QuotaLimits.TimeLimit.HighPart = 0xffffffff;
256 
257  KeStackAttachProcess (&Process->Pcb, &ApcState);
258 
259  Status = MmQueryWorkingSetInformation (&PeakWorkingSetSize,
260  &WorkingSetSize,
261  &QuotaLimits.MinimumWorkingSetSize,
262  &QuotaLimits.MaximumWorkingSetSize,
263  &HardEnforcement);
264  KeUnstackDetachProcess (&ApcState);
265 
266  if (HardEnforcement & MM_WORKING_SET_MIN_HARD_ENABLE) {
267  QuotaLimits.Flags = QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MIN_ENABLE;
268  } else {
269  QuotaLimits.Flags = QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MIN_DISABLE;
270  }
271 
272  if (HardEnforcement & MM_WORKING_SET_MAX_HARD_ENABLE) {
273  QuotaLimits.Flags |= QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MAX_ENABLE;
274  } else {
275  QuotaLimits.Flags |= QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MAX_DISABLE;
276  }
277 
278  ObDereferenceObject (Process);
279 
280  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
281  return Status;
282  }
283  //
284  // Either of these may cause an access violation. The
285  // exception handler will return access violation as
286  // status code.
287  //
288 
289  try {
290  ASSERT (ProcessInformationLength <= sizeof (QuotaLimits));
291 
292  RtlCopyMemory (ProcessInformation, &QuotaLimits, ProcessInformationLength);
293 
294  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT (ReturnLength)) {
295  *ReturnLength = ProcessInformationLength;
296  }
297  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
298  Status = GetExceptionCode ();
299  }
300 
301  return Status;
302 }

304 NTSTATUS
305 PspQueryPooledQuotaLimits(
306  IN HANDLE ProcessHandle,
307  IN PROCESSINFOCLASS ProcessInformationClass,
308  OUT PVOID ProcessInformation,
309  IN ULONG ProcessInformationLength,
310  OUT PULONG ReturnLength OPTIONAL,
311  IN KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode
312  )
313 {
314  PEPROCESS Process;
315  NTSTATUS st;
316  PEPROCESS_QUOTA_BLOCK QuotaBlock;
317  POOLED_USAGE_AND_LIMITS UsageAndLimits;
318 
319  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER (ProcessInformationClass);
320 
321  if (ProcessInformationLength != (ULONG) sizeof (POOLED_USAGE_AND_LIMITS)) {
322  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
323  }
324 
325  st = ObReferenceObjectByHandle (ProcessHandle,
326  PROCESS_QUERY_INFORMATION,
327  PsProcessType,
328  PreviousMode,
329  &Process,
330  NULL);
331  if (!NT_SUCCESS (st)) {
332  return st;
333  }
334 
335 
336  QuotaBlock = Process->QuotaBlock;
337 
338  UsageAndLimits.PagedPoolLimit = QuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsPagedPool].Limit;
339  UsageAndLimits.NonPagedPoolLimit = QuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsNonPagedPool].Limit;
340  UsageAndLimits.PagefileLimit = QuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsPageFile].Limit;
341 
342 
343  UsageAndLimits.PagedPoolUsage = QuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsPagedPool].Usage;
344  UsageAndLimits.NonPagedPoolUsage = QuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsNonPagedPool].Usage;
345  UsageAndLimits.PagefileUsage = QuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsPageFile].Usage;
346 
347  UsageAndLimits.PeakPagedPoolUsage = QuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsPagedPool].Peak;
348  UsageAndLimits.PeakNonPagedPoolUsage = QuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsNonPagedPool].Peak;
349  UsageAndLimits.PeakPagefileUsage = QuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsPageFile].Peak;
350 
351  //
352  // Since the quota charge and return are lock free we may see Peak and Limit out of step.
353  // Usage <= Limit and Usage <= Peak
354  // Since Limit is adjusted up and down it does not hold that Peak <= Limit.
355  //
356 #define PSMAX(a,b) (((a) > (b))?(a):(b))
357 
358  UsageAndLimits.PagedPoolLimit = PSMAX (UsageAndLimits.PagedPoolLimit, UsageAndLimits.PagedPoolUsage);
359  UsageAndLimits.NonPagedPoolLimit = PSMAX (UsageAndLimits.NonPagedPoolLimit, UsageAndLimits.NonPagedPoolUsage);
360  UsageAndLimits.PagefileLimit = PSMAX (UsageAndLimits.PagefileLimit, UsageAndLimits.PagefileUsage);
361 
362  UsageAndLimits.PeakPagedPoolUsage = PSMAX (UsageAndLimits.PeakPagedPoolUsage, UsageAndLimits.PagedPoolUsage);
363  UsageAndLimits.PeakNonPagedPoolUsage = PSMAX (UsageAndLimits.PeakNonPagedPoolUsage, UsageAndLimits.NonPagedPoolUsage);
364  UsageAndLimits.PeakPagefileUsage = PSMAX (UsageAndLimits.PeakPagefileUsage, UsageAndLimits.PagefileUsage);
365 
366  ObDereferenceObject(Process);
367 
368  //
369  // Either of these may cause an access violation. The
370  // exception handler will return access violation as
371  // status code. No further cleanup needs to be done.
372  //
373 
374  try {
375  *(PPOOLED_USAGE_AND_LIMITS) ProcessInformation = UsageAndLimits;
376 
377  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(ReturnLength) ) {
378  *ReturnLength = sizeof(POOLED_USAGE_AND_LIMITS);
379  }
380  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
381  return GetExceptionCode ();
382  }
383 
384  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
385 }

388 NTSTATUS
389 PspSetPrimaryToken(
390  IN HANDLE ProcessHandle OPTIONAL,
391  IN PEPROCESS ProcessPointer OPTIONAL,
392  IN HANDLE TokenHandle OPTIONAL,
393  IN PACCESS_TOKEN TokenPointer OPTIONAL,
394  IN BOOLEAN PrivilegeChecked
395  )
396 /*++
397 
398  Sets the primary token for a process.
399  The token and process supplied can be either by
400  handle or by pointer.
401 
402 --*/
403 {
404  NTSTATUS Status;
405  BOOLEAN HasPrivilege;
406  BOOLEAN IsChildToken;
407  BOOLEAN IsSiblingToken;
408  PEPROCESS Process;
409  KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode;
410  ACCESS_MASK GrantedAccess;
411  PACCESS_TOKEN Token;
412 
413  //
414  // Check to see if the supplied token is a child of the caller's
415  // token. If so, we don't need to do the privilege check.
416  //
417 
418  PreviousMode = KeGetPreviousMode ();
419 
420  if (TokenPointer == NULL) {
421  //
422  // Reference the specified token, and make sure it can be assigned
423  // as a primary token.
424  //
425 
426  Status = ObReferenceObjectByHandle (TokenHandle,
427  TOKEN_ASSIGN_PRIMARY,
428  SeTokenObjectType,
429  PreviousMode,
430  &Token,
431  NULL);
432 
433  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
434  return Status;
435  }
436  } else {
437  Token = TokenPointer;
438  }
439 
440  //
441  // If the privilege check has already been done (when the token was
442  // assign to a job for example). We don't want to do it here.
443  //
444  if (!PrivilegeChecked) {
445  Status = SeIsChildTokenByPointer (Token,
446  &IsChildToken);
447 
448  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
449  goto exit_and_deref_token;
450  }
451 
452  if (!IsChildToken) {
453 
454  Status = SeIsSiblingTokenByPointer (Token,
455  &IsSiblingToken);
456 
457  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
458  goto exit_and_deref_token;
459  }
460 
461  if (!IsSiblingToken) {
462 
463  //
464  // SeCheckPrivilegedObject will perform auditing as appropriate
465  //
466 
467  HasPrivilege = SeCheckPrivilegedObject (SeAssignPrimaryTokenPrivilege,
468  ProcessHandle,
469  PROCESS_SET_INFORMATION,
470  PreviousMode);
471 
472  if (!HasPrivilege) {
473 
474  Status = STATUS_PRIVILEGE_NOT_HELD;
475 
476  goto exit_and_deref_token;
477  }
478  }
479 
480  }
481 
482  }
483 
484  if (ProcessPointer == NULL) {
485  Status = ObReferenceObjectByHandle (ProcessHandle,
486  PROCESS_SET_INFORMATION,
487  PsProcessType,
488  PreviousMode,
489  &Process,
490  NULL);
491 
492  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
493 
494  goto exit_and_deref_token;
495  }
496  } else {
497  Process = ProcessPointer;
498  }
499 
500 
501  //
502  // Check for proper access to the token, and assign the primary
503  // token for the process.
504  //
505 
506  Status = PspAssignPrimaryToken (Process, NULL, Token);
507 
508  //
509  // Recompute the process's access to itself for use
510  // with the CurrentProcess() pseudo handle.
511  //
512 
513  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
514 
515  NTSTATUS accesst;
516  BOOLEAN AccessCheck;
517  BOOLEAN MemoryAllocated;
518  PSECURITY_DESCRIPTOR SecurityDescriptor;
519  SECURITY_SUBJECT_CONTEXT SubjectContext;
520 
521  Status = ObGetObjectSecurity (Process,
522  &SecurityDescriptor,
523  &MemoryAllocated);
524 
525  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
526  SubjectContext.ProcessAuditId = Process;
527  SubjectContext.PrimaryToken = PsReferencePrimaryToken (Process);
528  SubjectContext.ClientToken = NULL;
529  AccessCheck = SeAccessCheck (SecurityDescriptor,
530  &SubjectContext,
531  FALSE,
532  MAXIMUM_ALLOWED,
533  0,
534  NULL,
535  &PsProcessType->TypeInfo.GenericMapping,
536  PreviousMode,
537  &GrantedAccess,
538  &accesst);
539 
540  PsDereferencePrimaryTokenEx(Process, SubjectContext.PrimaryToken);
541  ObReleaseObjectSecurity (SecurityDescriptor,
542  MemoryAllocated);
543 
544  if (!AccessCheck) {
545  GrantedAccess = 0;
546  }
547 
548  //
549  // To keep consistency with process creation, grant these
550  // bits otherwise CreateProcessAsUser messes up really badly for
551  // restricted tokens and we end up with a process that has no
552  // access to itself when new token is set on the suspended
553  // process.
554  //
555  GrantedAccess |= (PROCESS_VM_OPERATION | PROCESS_VM_READ |
556  PROCESS_VM_WRITE | PROCESS_QUERY_INFORMATION |
557  PROCESS_TERMINATE | PROCESS_CREATE_THREAD |
558  PROCESS_DUP_HANDLE | PROCESS_CREATE_PROCESS |
559  PROCESS_SET_INFORMATION | STANDARD_RIGHTS_ALL |
560  PROCESS_SET_QUOTA);
561 
562  Process->GrantedAccess = GrantedAccess;
563  }
564  //
565  // Since the process token is being set,
566  // Set the device map for process to NULL.
567  // During the next reference to the process' device map,
568  // the object manager will set the device map for the process
569  //
570  if (ObIsLUIDDeviceMapsEnabled() != 0) {
571  ObDereferenceDeviceMap( Process );
572  }
573  }
574 
575  if (ProcessPointer == NULL) {
576  ObDereferenceObject (Process);
577  }
578 
579 exit_and_deref_token:
580 
581  if (TokenPointer == NULL) {
582  ObDereferenceObject (Token);
583  }
584 
585  return Status;
586 }

589 NTSTATUS
590 NtQueryInformationProcess(
591  __in HANDLE ProcessHandle,
592  __in PROCESSINFOCLASS ProcessInformationClass,
593  __out_bcount(ProcessInformationLength) PVOID ProcessInformation,
594  __in ULONG ProcessInformationLength,
595  __out_opt PULONG ReturnLength
596  )
597 {
598  PEPROCESS Process;
599  KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode;
600  NTSTATUS st;
601  PROCESS_BASIC_INFORMATION BasicInfo;
602  VM_COUNTERS_EX VmCounters;
603  IO_COUNTERS IoCounters;
604  KERNEL_USER_TIMES SysUserTime;
605  HANDLE DebugPort;
606  ULONG ExecuteOptions;
607  ULONG HandleCount;
608  ULONG DefaultHardErrorMode;
609  ULONG DisableBoost;
610  ULONG BreakOnTerminationEnabled;
611  PPROCESS_DEVICEMAP_INFORMATION DeviceMapInfo;
612  PROCESS_SESSION_INFORMATION SessionInfo;
613  PROCESS_PRIORITY_CLASS PriorityClass;
614  ULONG_PTR Wow64Info;
615  ULONG Flags;
616  PUNICODE_STRING pTempNameInfo;
617  SIZE_T MinimumWorkingSetSize;
618  SIZE_T MaximumWorkingSetSize;
619  ULONG HardEnforcement;
620  KAPC_STATE ApcState;
621  ULONG TotalKernel;
622  ULONG TotalUser;
623  KPROCESS_VALUES Values;
624 
625  PAGED_CODE();
626 
627  //
628  // Get previous processor mode and probe output argument if necessary.
629  //
630 
631  PreviousMode = KeGetPreviousMode();
632  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
633  try {
634  //
635  // Since these functions don't change any state thats not reversible
636  // in the error paths we only probe the output buffer for write access.
637  // This improves performance by not touching the buffer multiple times
638  // And only writing the portions of the buffer that change.
639  //
640  ProbeForRead (ProcessInformation,
641  ProcessInformationLength,
642  sizeof (ULONG));
643 
644  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT (ReturnLength)) {
645  ProbeForWriteUlong (ReturnLength);
646  }
647  } except(EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
648  return GetExceptionCode();
649  }
650  }
651 
652  //
653  // Check argument validity.
654  //
655 
656  switch ( ProcessInformationClass ) {
657 
658  case ProcessImageFileName:
659  {
660  ULONG LengthNeeded = 0;
661 
662  st = ObReferenceObjectByHandle (ProcessHandle,
663  PROCESS_QUERY_INFORMATION,
664  PsProcessType,
665  PreviousMode,
666  &Process,
667  NULL);
668 
669  if (!NT_SUCCESS (st)) {
670  return st;
671  }
672 
673  //
674  // SeLocateProcessImageName will allocate space for a UNICODE_STRING and point pTempNameInfo
675  // at that string. This memory will be freed later in the routine.
676  //
677 
678  st = SeLocateProcessImageName (Process, &pTempNameInfo);
679 
680  if (!NT_SUCCESS(st)) {
681  ObDereferenceObject(Process);
682  return st;
683  }
684 
685  LengthNeeded = sizeof(UNICODE_STRING) + pTempNameInfo->MaximumLength;
686 
687  //
688  // Either of these may cause an access violation. The
689  // exception handler will return access violation as
690  // status code. No further cleanup needs to be done.
691  //
692 
693  try {
694 
695  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(ReturnLength) ) {
696  *ReturnLength = LengthNeeded;
697  }
698 
699  if (ProcessInformationLength >= LengthNeeded) {
700  RtlCopyMemory(
701  ProcessInformation,
702  pTempNameInfo,
703  sizeof(UNICODE_STRING) + pTempNameInfo->MaximumLength
704  );
705  ((PUNICODE_STRING) ProcessInformation)->Buffer = (PWSTR)((PUCHAR) ProcessInformation + sizeof(UNICODE_STRING));
706 
707  } else {
708  st = STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
709  }
710 
711  } except(EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
712  st = GetExceptionCode ();
713  }
714 
715  ObDereferenceObject(Process);
716  ExFreePool( pTempNameInfo );
717 
718  return st;
719 
720  }
721 
722  case ProcessWorkingSetWatch:
723 
724  return PspQueryWorkingSetWatch (ProcessHandle,
725  ProcessInformationClass,
726  ProcessInformation,
727  ProcessInformationLength,
728  ReturnLength,
729  PreviousMode);
730 
731  case ProcessBasicInformation:
732 
733  if (ProcessInformationLength != (ULONG) sizeof(PROCESS_BASIC_INFORMATION)) {
734  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
735  }
736 
737  st = ObReferenceObjectByHandle (ProcessHandle,
738  PROCESS_QUERY_INFORMATION,
739  PsProcessType,
740  PreviousMode,
741  &Process,
742  NULL);
743  if (!NT_SUCCESS (st)) {
744  return st;
745  }
746 
747  BasicInfo.ExitStatus = Process->ExitStatus;
748  BasicInfo.PebBaseAddress = Process->Peb;
749  BasicInfo.AffinityMask = Process->Pcb.Affinity;
750  BasicInfo.BasePriority = Process->Pcb.BasePriority;
751  BasicInfo.UniqueProcessId = (ULONG_PTR)Process->UniqueProcessId;
752  BasicInfo.InheritedFromUniqueProcessId = (ULONG_PTR)Process->InheritedFromUniqueProcessId;
753 
754  ObDereferenceObject(Process);
755 
756  //
757  // Either of these may cause an access violation. The
758  // exception handler will return access violation as
759  // status code. No further cleanup needs to be done.
760  //
761 
762  try {
763  *(PPROCESS_BASIC_INFORMATION) ProcessInformation = BasicInfo;
764 
765  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT (ReturnLength) ) {
766  *ReturnLength = sizeof(PROCESS_BASIC_INFORMATION);
767  }

1561  }
1562 
1563  ObDereferenceObject(Process);
1564  return st;
1565  }
1566 
1567  case ProcessExecuteFlags:
1568 
1569  //
1570  // This code queries the execution flags for the current process.
1571  //
1572 
1573  if (ProcessInformationLength != sizeof (ULONG)) {
1574  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
1575  }
1576 
1577  if (ProcessHandle != NtCurrentProcess ()) {
1578  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
1579  }
1580 
1581  st = MmGetExecuteOptions (&ExecuteOptions);
1582  if (NT_SUCCESS(st)) {
1583  try {
1584  *(PULONG)ProcessInformation = ExecuteOptions;
1585  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT (ReturnLength)) {
1586  *ReturnLength = sizeof(ULONG);
1587  }
1588  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
1589  st = GetExceptionCode ();
1590  }
1591  }
1592 
1593  return st;
1594 
1595  case ProcessCookie: {
1596  ULONG Cookie;
1597  LARGE_INTEGER Time;
1598  PKPRCB Prcb;
1599 
1600 
1601  if (ProcessInformationLength != sizeof (ULONG)) {
1602  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
1603  }
1604 
1605  if (ProcessHandle != NtCurrentProcess ()) {
1606  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
1607  }
1608 
1609  Process = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
1610 
1611  while (1) {
1612  Cookie = Process->Cookie;
1613  if (Cookie != 0) {
1614 
1615  try {
1616  *(PULONG)ProcessInformation = Process->Cookie;
1617 
1618  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT (ReturnLength)) {
1619  *ReturnLength = sizeof (ULONG);
1620  }
1621  } except(EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
1622  return GetExceptionCode ();
1623  }
1624 
1625  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
1626 
1627  } else {
1628  KeQuerySystemTime (&Time);
1629  Prcb = KeGetCurrentPrcb ();
1630  Cookie = Time.LowPart ^ Time.HighPart ^ Prcb->InterruptTime ^ Prcb->KeSystemCalls;
1631  InterlockedCompareExchange ((PLONG)&Process->Cookie, Cookie, 0);
1632  }
1633  }
1634  }
1635 
1636  case ProcessImageInformation:
1637 
1638  //
1639  // This code queries the section image information for the current
1640  // process.
1641  //
1642 
1643  if (ProcessInformationLength != sizeof (SECTION_IMAGE_INFORMATION)) {
1644  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
1645  }
1646 
1647  if (ProcessHandle != NtCurrentProcess ()) {
1648  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
1649  }
1650 
1651  try {
1652  MmGetImageInformation((PSECTION_IMAGE_INFORMATION)ProcessInformation);
1653  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT (ReturnLength)) {
1654  *ReturnLength = sizeof (SECTION_IMAGE_INFORMATION);
1655  }
1656  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
1657  return GetExceptionCode ();
1658  }
1659 
1660  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
1661 
1662  default:
1663  return STATUS_INVALID_INFO_CLASS;
1664  }
1665 }

1698 NTSTATUS
1699 PspSetQuotaLimits(
1700  IN HANDLE ProcessHandle,
1701  IN PROCESSINFOCLASS ProcessInformationClass,
1702  IN PVOID ProcessInformation,
1703  IN ULONG ProcessInformationLength,
1704  IN KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode
1705  )
1706 {
1707  PEPROCESS Process;
1708  PETHREAD CurrentThread;
1709  QUOTA_LIMITS_EX RequestedLimits;
1710  PEPROCESS_QUOTA_BLOCK NewQuotaBlock;
1711  NTSTATUS st, ReturnStatus;
1712  BOOLEAN OkToIncrease, IgnoreError;
1713  PEJOB Job;
1714  KAPC_STATE ApcState;
1715  ULONG EnableHardLimits;
1716  BOOLEAN PurgeRequest, UnprivilegedOperation, PrivilegeUsed, FreeCtx, IncreasePerformed;
1717  PRIV_CHECK_CTX PrivCtx;
1718 
1719 
1720  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER (ProcessInformationClass);
1721 
1722  try {
1723 
1724  if (ProcessInformationLength == sizeof (QUOTA_LIMITS)) {
1725  RtlCopyMemory (&RequestedLimits,
1726  ProcessInformation,
1727  sizeof (QUOTA_LIMITS));
1728  RequestedLimits.Reserved1 = 0;
1729  RequestedLimits.Reserved2 = 0;
1730  RequestedLimits.Reserved3 = 0;
1731  RequestedLimits.Reserved4 = 0;
1732  RequestedLimits.Reserved5 = 0;
1733  RequestedLimits.Flags = 0;
1734  } else if (ProcessInformationLength == sizeof (QUOTA_LIMITS_EX)) {
1735  RequestedLimits = *(PQUOTA_LIMITS_EX) ProcessInformation;
1736  } else {
1737  return STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
1738  }
1739 
1740  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
1741  return GetExceptionCode ();
1742  }
1743 
1744  //
1745  // All unused flags must be zero
1746  //
1747  if (RequestedLimits.Flags & ~(QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MAX_ENABLE|QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MAX_DISABLE|
1748  QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MIN_ENABLE|QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MIN_DISABLE)) {
1749  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
1750  }
1751 
1752  //
1753  // Disallow both enable and disable bits set at the same time.
1754  //
1755  if (PS_TEST_ALL_BITS_SET (RequestedLimits.Flags, QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MIN_ENABLE|QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MIN_DISABLE) ||
1756  PS_TEST_ALL_BITS_SET (RequestedLimits.Flags, QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MAX_ENABLE|QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MAX_DISABLE)) {
1757  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
1758  }
1759 
1760  //
1761  // See if we are changing the hard limits or not
1762  //
1763 
1764  EnableHardLimits = 0;
1765 
1766  if (RequestedLimits.Flags&QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MIN_ENABLE) {
1767  EnableHardLimits = MM_WORKING_SET_MIN_HARD_ENABLE;
1768  } else if (RequestedLimits.Flags&QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MIN_DISABLE) {
1769  EnableHardLimits = MM_WORKING_SET_MIN_HARD_DISABLE;
1770  }
1771 
1772  if (RequestedLimits.Flags&QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MAX_ENABLE) {
1773  EnableHardLimits |= MM_WORKING_SET_MAX_HARD_ENABLE;
1774  } else if (RequestedLimits.Flags&QUOTA_LIMITS_HARDWS_MAX_DISABLE) {
1775  EnableHardLimits |= MM_WORKING_SET_MAX_HARD_DISABLE;
1776  }
1777 
1778 
1779  //
1780  // All reserved fields must be zero
1781  //
1782  if (RequestedLimits.Reserved1 != 0 || RequestedLimits.Reserved2 != 0 ||
1783  RequestedLimits.Reserved3 != 0 || RequestedLimits.Reserved4 != 0 ||
1784  RequestedLimits.Reserved5 != 0) {
1785  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
1786  }
1787 
1788 
1789  st = ObReferenceObjectByHandle (ProcessHandle,
1790  PROCESS_SET_QUOTA,
1791  PsProcessType,
1792  PreviousMode,
1793  &Process,
1794  NULL);
1795 
1796  if (!NT_SUCCESS (st)) {
1797  return st;
1798  }
1799 
1800  CurrentThread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
1801 
1802  //
1803  // Now we are ready to set the quota limits for the process
1804  //
1805  // If the process already has a quota block, then all we allow
1806  // is working set changes.
1807  //
1808  // If the process has no quota block, all that can be done is a
1809  // quota set operation.
1810  //
1811  // If a quota field is zero, we pick the value.
1812  //
1813  // Setting quotas requires the SeIncreaseQuotaPrivilege (except for
1814  // working set size since this is only advisory).
1815  //
1816 
1817 
1818  ReturnStatus = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1819 
1820  if ((Process->QuotaBlock == &PspDefaultQuotaBlock) &&
1821  (RequestedLimits.MinimumWorkingSetSize == 0 || RequestedLimits.MaximumWorkingSetSize == 0)) {
1822 
1823  //
1824  // You must have a privilege to assign quotas
1825  //
1826 
1827  if (!SeSinglePrivilegeCheck (SeIncreaseQuotaPrivilege, PreviousMode)) {
1828  ObDereferenceObject (Process);
1829  return STATUS_PRIVILEGE_NOT_HELD;
1830  }
1831 
1832  NewQuotaBlock = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool, sizeof(*NewQuotaBlock), 'bQsP');
1833  if (NewQuotaBlock == NULL) {
1834  ObDereferenceObject (Process);
1835  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
1836  }
1837 
1838  RtlZeroMemory (NewQuotaBlock, sizeof (*NewQuotaBlock));
1839 
1840  //
1841  // Initialize the quota block
1842  //
1843  NewQuotaBlock->ReferenceCount = 1;
1844  NewQuotaBlock->ProcessCount = 1;
1845 
1846  NewQuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsNonPagedPool].Peak = Process->QuotaPeak[PsNonPagedPool];
1847  NewQuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsPagedPool].Peak = Process->QuotaPeak[PsPagedPool];
1848  NewQuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsPageFile].Peak = Process->QuotaPeak[PsPageFile];
1849 
1850  //
1851  // Now compute limits
1852  //
1853 
1854  //
1855  // Get the defaults that the system would pick.
1856  //
1857 
1858  NewQuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsPagedPool].Limit = PspDefaultPagedLimit;
1859  NewQuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsNonPagedPool].Limit = PspDefaultNonPagedLimit;
1860  NewQuotaBlock->QuotaEntry[PsPageFile].Limit = PspDefaultPagefileLimit;
1861 
1862  // Everything is set. Now double check to quota block field
1863  // If we still have no quota block then assign and succeed.
1864  // Otherwise punt.
1865  //
1866 
1867  if (InterlockedCompareExchangePointer (&Process->QuotaBlock,
1868  NewQuotaBlock,
1869  &PspDefaultQuotaBlock) != &PspDefaultQuotaBlock) {
1870  ExFreePool (NewQuotaBlock);
1871  } else {
1872  PspInsertQuotaBlock (NewQuotaBlock);
1873  }
1874 
1875 
1876  } else {
1877 
1878  //
1879  // Only allow a working set size change
1880  //
1881 
1882  if (RequestedLimits.MinimumWorkingSetSize &&
1883  RequestedLimits.MaximumWorkingSetSize) {
1884 
1885  //
1886  // See if the caller just wants to purge the working set.
1887  // This is an unprivileged operation.
1888  //
1889  if (RequestedLimits.MinimumWorkingSetSize == (SIZE_T)-1 &&
1890  RequestedLimits.MaximumWorkingSetSize == (SIZE_T)-1) {
1891  PurgeRequest = TRUE;
1892  OkToIncrease = FALSE;
1893  FreeCtx = FALSE;
1894  } else {
1895  PurgeRequest = FALSE;
1896 
1897  OkToIncrease = (BOOLEAN) PspSinglePrivCheck (SeIncreaseBasePriorityPrivilege, PreviousMode, &PrivCtx);
1898  FreeCtx = TRUE;
1899  }
1900 
1901  PrivilegeUsed = FALSE;
1902  do {
1903  IgnoreError = FALSE;
1904  UnprivilegedOperation = FALSE;
1905 
1906  KeStackAttachProcess (&Process->Pcb, &ApcState);
1907 
1908 
1909  KeEnterGuardedRegionThread (&CurrentThread->Tcb);
1910 
1911  Job = Process->Job;
1912  if (Job != NULL) {
1913  ExAcquireResourceExclusiveLite (&Job->JobLock, TRUE);
1914 
1915  if (Job->LimitFlags & JOB_OBJECT_LIMIT_WORKINGSET) {
1916  //
1917  // Don't let a process in a job change if job limits are applied
1918  // except purge requests which can always be done.
1919  //
1920 
1921  EnableHardLimits = MM_WORKING_SET_MAX_HARD_ENABLE;
1922  OkToIncrease = TRUE;
1923  UnprivilegedOperation = TRUE;
1924  IgnoreError = TRUE; // we must always set enforcement value
1925 
1926  if (!PurgeRequest) {
1927  RequestedLimits.MinimumWorkingSetSize = Job->MinimumWorkingSetSize;
1928  RequestedLimits.MaximumWorkingSetSize = Job->MaximumWorkingSetSize;
1929  }
1930  }
1931 
1932  PspLockWorkingSetChangeExclusiveUnsafe ();
1933 
1934  ExReleaseResourceLite (&Job->JobLock);
1935  }
1936 
1937  ReturnStatus = MmAdjustWorkingSetSizeEx (RequestedLimits.MinimumWorkingSetSize,
1938  RequestedLimits.MaximumWorkingSetSize,
1939  FALSE,
1940  OkToIncrease,
1941  EnableHardLimits,
1942  &IncreasePerformed);
1943 
1944  if (!NT_SUCCESS (ReturnStatus) && IgnoreError) {
1945  MmEnforceWorkingSetLimit (Process,
1946  EnableHardLimits);
1947  }
1948 
1949  if (Job != NULL) {
1950  PspUnlockWorkingSetChangeExclusiveUnsafe ();
1951  }
1952 
1953  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&CurrentThread->Tcb);
1954 
1955  KeUnstackDetachProcess (&ApcState);
1956 
1957  if (IncreasePerformed && !UnprivilegedOperation) {
1958  PrivilegeUsed = TRUE;
1959  }
1960 
1961  //
1962  // We loop here in case this process was added to a job
1963  // after we checked but before we set the limits
1964  //
1965 
1966  } while (Process->Job != Job);
1967 
1968  if (FreeCtx) {
1969  PspSinglePrivCheckAudit (PrivilegeUsed,
1970  &PrivCtx);
1971  }
1972  }
1973  }
1974 
1975  ObDereferenceObject(Process);
1976 
1977  return ReturnStatus;
1978 }

3040 NTSTATUS
3041 NtQueryInformationThread(
3042  __in HANDLE ThreadHandle,
3043  __in THREADINFOCLASS ThreadInformationClass,
3044  __out_bcount(ThreadInformationLength) PVOID ThreadInformation,
3045  __in ULONG ThreadInformationLength,
3046  __out_opt PULONG ReturnLength
3047  )
3048 
3049 /*++
3050 
3051 Routine Description:
3052 
3053  This function queries the state of a thread object and returns the
3054  requested information in the specified record structure.
3055 
3056 Arguments:
3057 
3058  ThreadHandle - Supplies a handle to a thread object.
3059 
3060  ThreadInformationClass - Supplies the class of information being
3061  requested.
3062 
3063  ThreadInformation - Supplies a pointer to a record that is to
3064  receive the requested information.
3065 
3066  ThreadInformationLength - Supplies the length of the record that is
3067  to receive the requested information.
3068 
3069  ReturnLength - Supplies an optional pointer to a variable that is to
3070  receive the actual length of information that is returned.
3071 
3072 --*/
3073 
3074 {
3075 
3076  LARGE_INTEGER PerformanceCount;
3077  PETHREAD Thread;
3078  PEPROCESS Process;
3079  ULONG LastThread;
3080  KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode;
3081  NTSTATUS st;
3082  THREAD_BASIC_INFORMATION BasicInfo;
3083  KERNEL_USER_TIMES SysUserTime;
3084  PVOID Win32StartAddressValue;
3085  ULONG DisableBoost;
3086  ULONG IoPending ;
3087  ULONG BreakOnTerminationEnabled;
3088  PETHREAD CurrentThread;
3089  ULONG ThreadTerminated;
3090  //
3091  // Get previous processor mode and probe output argument if necessary.
3092  //
3093 
3094  PAGED_CODE();
3095 
3096  CurrentThread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
3097 
3098  PreviousMode = KeGetPreviousModeByThread (&CurrentThread->Tcb);
3099 
3100  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
3101  try {
3102  //
3103  // Since these functions don't change any state thats not reversible
3104  // in the error paths we only probe the output buffer for write access.
3105  // This improves performance by not touching the buffer multiple times
3106  // And only writing the portions of the buffer that change.
3107  //
3108 
3109  ProbeForRead (ThreadInformation,
3110  ThreadInformationLength,
3111  sizeof(ULONG));
3112 
3113  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT( ReturnLength)) {
3114  ProbeForWriteUlong (ReturnLength);
3115  }
3116  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
